 of more recent claims according to which complex syntax is not a universal property of all living languages, the issue of how to detect and define syntactic complexity has been revived with a combination of classical and new arguments. This volume contains contributions about the formal complexity of natural language, about specific issues of clausal embedding, and about syntactic complexity in terms of grammar-external interfaces in the domain of language acquisition.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aFormalization (Linguistics) 0aFormalization (Linguistics). 0aGenerative grammar. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalvClauses. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalvSyntax. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxClauses. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxSyntax. 4aClausal Embedding. 4aGrammar Theory. 4aInterface Syntax. 4aSyntactic Complexity. 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBayer, Josef, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTrotzke, Andreas , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015010120 cprintz978161451785640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451790040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614517900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781614517900.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  a